articles.title: Blakstad starts at Spurs with unfinished WSL business
articles.summary: Tottenham's new signing Julie Blakstad is aiming to make her mark on the Women's Super League second time around after a difficult spell with Manchester City.

articles.title: Falkirk will keep 'foot to the floor' in top six bid
articles.summary: A 2-0 win at St Mirren takes Falkirk to 30 points as manager John McGlynn's promoted side continue to impress.

articles.title: Ford drives positivity but Livi spurn big chance
articles.summary: David Martindale bemoans a missed opportunity in Livingston's 1-1 Premiership draw against Kilmarnock, but chairman Calvin Ford insists he has 'complete belief' they will escape their current predicam...

articles.title: 'He is here with us' - Macclesfield make FA Cup history on emotional day
articles.summary: Non-league Macclesfield made FA Cup history by knocking out holders Crystal Palace on a memorable but emotional day - their victory achieved against a backdrop of tragedy.

articles.title: Another door closes for Spurs and Frank with damaging FA Cup exit
articles.summary: After Spurs' damaging FA Cup exit at home to Aston Villa, chief football writer Phil McNulty asks how long can head coach Thomas Frank survive?

articles.title: 'Humble' Semenyo steals show in FA Cup mauling
articles.summary: Antoine Semenyo signed off at Bournemouth in fairytale fashion and makes start to life at Manchester City in a similarly dreamy manner during 10-1 FA Cup win over League One Exeter City.

articles.title: Frank's failing Spurs knocked out of FA Cup by Aston Villa
articles.summary: Goals from Emiliano Buendia and Morgan Rogers knock a wasteful Tottenham Hotspur side out of the FA Cup to pile more pressure on manager Thomas Frank.

articles.title: Newcastle win on penalties after epic six-goal thriller
articles.summary: Newcastle United and Bournemouth play out a six-goal thriller, after a Harvey Barnes goal in the 118th minute is cancelled out by Marcus Tavernier's equaliser minutes later, with Newcastle progressing...

articles.title: Fletcher emerges as winner from week of turmoil at Man Utd
articles.summary: No matter who is appointed Manchester United caretaker manager, Darren Fletcher has emerged as one of the big winners from a week of turmoil at Old Trafford.

articles.title: Rosenior wins first game as Chelsea thrash Charlton
articles.summary: Liam Rosenior begins his reign as Chelsea head coach by overseeing a dominant display that saw off Championship side Charlton in the FA Cup third round.

articles.title: Non-league Macclesfield stun FA Cup holders Crystal Palace
articles.summary: Sixth-tier Macclesfield FC beat reigning champions Crystal Palace. With 117 places between the teams, it's the biggest upset in FA Cup history.

articles.title: 'It's double figures' - Manchester City score 10 as they thrash Exeter
articles.summary: Seven-time winners Manchester City cruise into the fourth round of the FA Cup by thrashing League One side Exeter City 10-1, with new signing Antoine Semenyo scoring a debut goal at Etihad Stadium.

articles.title: Strand Larsen scores hat-trick as Wolves thrash Shrewsbury
articles.summary: Striker Jorgen Strand Larsen's hat-trick ends his Wolves goal drought as he fires them past League Two Shrewsbury into the FA Cup fourth round.

articles.title: Barnes brace helps Burnley to victory over Millwall
articles.summary: Premier League strugglers Burnley score three first-half goals as they sweep aside Championship team Millwall to reach the fourth round of the FA Cup.

articles.title: Supersub Wilson sparks Fulham comeback against Middlesbrough
articles.summary: Harry Wilson came on to help his side avoid a potential upset, as Fulham score three second half goals to beat Middlesbrough.

articles.summary: Jaden Philogene's exquisite first-half strike helps Championship promotion hopefuls Ipswich Town to victory over League One side Blackpool in the FA Cup third round.
